  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6778.45 sitting just below the GEX flip at 6783, dealers are in positive gamma territory and will be selling any push higher while buying dips - classic PIN regime stabilization. The massive GEX surge (44.8% in 1-min) indicates heavy options flow just hit, likely from institutional hedging that's created a formidable resistance wall from 6780-6800 with over 50B in positive gamma at the 6800 strike. Dealers will aggressively fade moves toward 6800 while providing support around 6770 where they flip to negative gamma and become forced buyers.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect choppy action capped near 6800 with decent support around 6770.",
